cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use hermes-prime in research or production tooling, please cite it."
title: "hermes-prime: a session-priming bootstrap for Claude Code"
abstract: "A bash bootstrap that injects a versioned CLAUDE.md fragment into a project so a fresh Claude Code session opens with grounding triggers, convention pointers, and tool-map already in scope. Per-project, marker-anchored, idempotent, fully reversible."
